==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛnd|-ɛnd]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|wends|wending|wended|wended}} (''transitive'' and ''intransitive'')
# To [[go]] or [[proceed]] [[along]] some [[course]] or [[way]].
#: ''We '''wended''' our weary way westward''

====Usage notes====
The past tense of '''[[wend]]''' is '''[[wended]]'''.  Originally it was '''[[went]]''', however that has come to be the past tense of '''[[go]]''', and using it as the past tense of '''[[wend]]''' would be considered archaic.

